member.remarks: The LCD is the least common multiple of the two denominators. For instance, the LCD of {1/2, 1/4} is 4 because the least common multiple of 2 and 4 is 4. Likewise, the LCD of {1/2, 1/3} is 6. To find the LCD: 1) Find the Greatest Common Divisor (GCD) of the denominators 2) Multiply the denominators together 3) Divide the product of the denominators by the GCD
